Here's the comprehensive draft for the employment terms and conditions and policies for Keplix, formatted in Markdown:

```markdown
# Keplix Employment Terms and Conditions

## Introduction

Welcome to Keplix! We are delighted to have you as part of our team. This document outlines the terms and conditions of your employment with Keplix. Please read these terms carefully and ensure you understand them. If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to the HR department.

## 1. Employment Terms

### 1.1 Employment At-Will

Your employment with Keplix is on an at-will basis, as per Indian labor laws. This means that either you or Keplix may terminate the employment relationship at any time, with or without cause or notice, subject to applicable laws.

### 1.2 Position and Duties

You are employed in the position of [Position Title] and will perform the duties and responsibilities as outlined in your job description. Your role may evolve as the company grows, and you may be required to undertake additional or different duties as reasonably requested by the company.

### 1.3 Working Hours

Your standard working hours will be from [Start Time] to [End Time], [Number] days a week, in accordance with the Factories Act, 1948, and the Shops and Establishments Act applicable in your state. Flexibility in working hours may be required based on business needs. Any changes to your working hours will be communicated to you in advance.

### 1.4 Compensation

You will be compensated as outlined in your offer letter. This includes your base salary, bonus structure, and any equity options if applicable. Salary reviews will be conducted annually, and any adjustments will be based on performance and market conditions.

### 1.5 Benefits

As a Keplix employee, you are eligible for the benefits outlined in our benefits policy. These include health insurance, retirement plans, and any other benefits as detailed in your offer letter and our employee handbook, in compliance with the Employee Provident Fund (EPF) and the Employees' State Insurance (ESI) schemes.

## 2. Company Policies

### 2.1 Code of Conduct

All employees are expected to adhere to the highest standards of professional conduct. This includes, but is not limited to, treating colleagues with respect, maintaining confidentiality, and adhering to all company policies and procedures.

### 2.2 Confidentiality

You are required to maintain the confidentiality of all proprietary information, trade secrets, and other confidential information related to Keplix and its clients. This obligation continues even after the termination of your employment.

### 2.3 Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA)

As a condition of your employment, you will be required to sign an NDA to protect the companyâ€™s intellectual property and confidential information.

### 2.4 Conflict of Interest

Employees must avoid any activities or relationships that could create a conflict of interest with the company. If you are unsure whether an activity constitutes a conflict of interest, please consult with the HR department.

## 3. Workplace Environment

### 3.1 Equal Opportunity Employment

Keplix is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to providing a workplace free from discrimination and harassment, in accordance with the provisions of the Equal Remuneration Act, 1976, and the Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition, and Redressal) Act, 2013.

### 3.2 Health and Safety

We are committed to providing a safe and healthy work environment. Employees are expected to adhere to all health and safety policies and report any unsafe conditions or practices to the management, in compliance with the Factories Act, 1948, and the relevant Shops and Establishments Act.

### 3.3 Remote Work Policy

Keplix supports flexible working arrangements, including remote work, as long as it aligns with business needs. Specific remote work arrangements will be outlined in your employment contract or communicated by your supervisor.

## 4. Leave Policies

### 4.1 Paid Time Off (PTO)

Employees are entitled to paid time off, which includes vacation days, personal days, and sick leave, in accordance with the Factories Act, 1948, and the relevant Shops and Establishments Act. The specifics of your PTO entitlement will be detailed in your offer letter and employee handbook.

### 4.2 Maternity and Paternity Leave

Keplix provides maternity and paternity leave in accordance with the Maternity Benefit Act, 1961, and the Paternity Leave policy, if applicable. Details of these policies are available in the employee handbook.

### 4.3 Other Leave

Employees may be entitled to other types of leave, such as bereavement leave, jury duty leave, and unpaid leave of absence, as outlined in the employee handbook, in compliance with applicable laws.

## 5. Termination

### 5.1 Voluntary Termination

If you wish to resign from your position, we request that you provide at least [Notice Period] notice, in compliance with the notice period requirements under the applicable labor laws. This allows for a smooth transition and handover of responsibilities.

### 5.2 Involuntary Termination

Keplix reserves the right to terminate your employment at any time, with or without cause or notice, in accordance with the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947, and other relevant laws. Reasons for termination may include, but are not limited to, poor performance, misconduct, or violation of company policies.

### 5.3 Exit Process

Upon termination, you are required to return all company property and settle any outstanding obligations. An exit interview may be conducted to gather feedback and ensure a smooth departure.

## 6. Dispute Resolution

### 6.1 Grievance Procedure

If you have any grievances or concerns related to your employment, please raise them with your immediate supervisor or the HR department. We are committed to addressing and resolving any issues in a fair and timely manner, in accordance with the Grievance Redressal Mechanism prescribed under the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947.

### 6.2 Arbitration

Any disputes arising out of or related to your employment with Keplix will be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the Indian Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996.

## 7. Amendments

Keplix reserves the right to amend these terms and conditions at any time. Any changes will be communicated to employees in writing and will take effect immediately unless stated otherwise.

## Conclusion

We are excited to have you as part of the Keplix team and look forward to a successful working relationship. If you have any questions or need further clarification on any of the above terms and conditions, please do not hesitate to contact the HR department.
```

Please ensure the content complies with local labor laws and regulations and have it reviewed by a legal professional before making it publicly available.
